               <p>JAMES ELY, I am a <rs id="t18230115-175-viclabel948" type="occupation">coal dealer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-175-victim1453 t18230115-175-viclabel948"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18230115-175-crimeloc949">Norton-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-175-crimeloc949" type="placeName" value="Norton-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-175-crimeloc949" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-175-off946 t18230115-175-crimeloc949"></join>. On the 13th of January, about half-past eleven o'clock, the prisoner came to my house with my brother's card - and said my brother would be obliged if I would lend him my great coat. I gave it him,</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230115-175-person1454">
                  JOHN 
                  ELY
               <interp inst="t18230115-175-person1454" type="surname" value="ELY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230115-175-person1454" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230115-175-person1454" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was in my service; I sent him to Hampstead, and told him to call and borrow my brother's great coat for me; he never came near me all day, so I went to my brother's, and at night met him in Holborn, with half a dozen girls, and asked what he had done with it; he said he had not had, nor seen it. I said, he had had it at half-past eleven o'clock; he said,</p>
               <p>"Well, a boy came running after me in Oxford-street, (who I believe to be your brother's boy) and asked me for it." I said my brother had not got a boy.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man ran after me in Oxford-street, and said he wanted Mr. Ely's coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18230115-175-verdict950" type="verdictDescription">
